        <h2 class="section-heading">FAQ</h2>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">Is this guide specific to my camera brand?</div>
            <div class="faq-a"><p>The guide covers general security steps that apply to all smart cameras, plus brand-specific instructions for Ring, Google Nest, Arlo, Wyze, Eufy, and Reolink &mdash; including where to find 2FA settings in each app. The WiFi section includes router-specific steps for TP-Link, Netgear, Eero, Google Wifi, Xfinity, and ASUS.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">I'm not technical at all. Will I be able to follow this?</div>
            <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. This guide is written for people who know how to install an app and follow step-by-step instructions. Every technical term is explained in plain English, and there's a glossary at the back for quick reference. If you can follow a recipe, you can follow this guide.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">Can't I just find this information free on YouTube?</div>
            <div class="faq-a"><p>You can find pieces of it scattered across dozens of videos, forum posts, and blog articles &mdash; some outdated, some overly technical, some contradicting each other. This guide puts everything in one place, in order, with a printable checklist. The value is not the information &mdash; it's having a single start-to-finish workflow you can trust and complete in one sitting.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">What format is the guide?</div>
            <div class="faq-a"><p>It's a professionally formatted PDF (approximately 22 pages) designed to be readable on screen or printed. The cheat sheet at the end is specifically designed for printing &mdash; keep it near your router for quarterly check-ups.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">Who wrote this guide?</div>
            <div class="faq-a"><p>This guide is published by Salish AI Security Lab, a cybersecurity research lab specializing in application security and threat detection. We build security frameworks used by organizations ranging from mid-market companies to enterprise. This consumer guide applies the same rigorous methodology to home network security.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <div class="faq-q">What if my camera brand isn't listed?</div>
